      "question1_answer": "This picture feels so dreamy. A girl is chilling on a yacht, soaking in the view of the open sea. She's probably feeling the cool breeze in her hair while watching the waves sparkle under the sun. The vibe is super calm, like she's just enjoying a peaceful moment far away from all the noise. Behind her, the ocean stretches endlessly, blending into the horizon where the sky shows off some gorgeous colors. It's the kind of scene that makes you wanna be there too.",
      "question2": "Tell us the last time you went to the sea?",
      "question2_answer": "The last time I went to the sea was about six months ago. I visited a beautiful coastal town with my family. We spent the day on the beach, enjoying the warm sun and refreshing breeze. We swam in the crystal-clear water and collected shells along the shore. In the evening, we watched the sunset over the ocean, which was absolutely breathtaking. It was a relaxing and memorable experience that I will always cherish.",
      "question3": "Why do some people dislike going to the sea?",
      "question3_answer": "Not everyone enjoys going to the sea, and there are several reasons for this. Some people are afraid of deep water or cannot swim, which makes them feel unsafe near the ocean. Others dislike the feel of sand on their skin or in their clothes, as it can be quite uncomfortable. The strong sun at the beach can also cause sunburn, which is painful and unpleasant. Additionally, some people simply prefer quieter environments, like the mountains or forests, and find the noise and crowds at the beach overwhelming."
